    • getAllSuperMethodsRecursive

      private void getAllSuperMethodsRecursive(Class<?> token, Set<Method> set)
      Recursive auxiliary method that is used in getAllSuperMethods(Class) method to get all methods that class must implement. Class have Set<Method>set as a parameter where we store methods. We put there all declared methods and then call this method for super interfaces.
      Parameters:
      token - given interface.
      set - set where we store methods.

    • main

      public static void main(String[] args)
      Main method of Implementor class. If there are 2 arguments, method will implement given interface and locate it in given path. If there are 3 arguments, method will create jar file in given path, and jar file will contain implementation of given interface.
      Parameters:
      args - command line arguments.
